WEBVTT

00:01.210 --> 00:02.950
Previously on Queen Sugar.

00:03.000 --> 00:05.207
I sold the mill
for 1% equity
in Landry Enterprises.

00:05.250 --> 00:07.377
Everything those people
put you through, put us through?

00:07.420 --> 00:08.626
It's what Daddy
would have wanted.

00:08.670 --> 00:11.252
-They killed him.
-And I'm gonna make them pay!

00:11.300 --> 00:13.086
So why are you here?

00:13.130 --> 00:14.711
Do you miss being around
your people that much?

00:14.760 --> 00:16.387
I've never really been
around my people.

00:16.430 --> 00:18.216
All of the articles
we discussed,

00:18.260 --> 00:20.387
they're no longer available
for your book.

00:20.430 --> 00:22.261
You could write about the black
farmers and their struggles.

00:22.310 --> 00:26.053
If you wouldn't mind,
I splurged on this.

00:26.110 --> 00:27.179
No more Remy.

00:27.230 --> 00:28.857
No more, darling.

00:42.870 --> 00:44.531
-Mommy!
-Yes, yes?

00:44.580 --> 00:47.538
-Look what I made you!
'[gasps] Oh, my gosh!

00:47.590 --> 00:50.957
-It's a coloring book.
-This is amazing.

00:51.010 --> 00:52.716
-You made this for me?
-Yes.

00:52.760 --> 00:54.751
That's Pickles, the gerbil
from our classroom.

00:54.800 --> 00:58.634
-So cute!
-That's him when he's swimming.

00:58.680 --> 01:01.387
And there's Papa
working on the farm.

01:01.430 --> 01:04.137
Oh, we're making
a bonfire on Friday.

01:04.190 --> 01:05.726
A bonfire? Why?

01:05.770 --> 01:08.352
Blue set up
a commemoration,

01:08.400 --> 01:10.607
celebrating Daddy's life.

01:10.650 --> 01:12.686
So we write messages
to Papa,

01:12.740 --> 01:15.732
we put them in the fire
and then send them to heaven.

01:15.780 --> 01:18.271
-Oh!
-Are you coming?

01:22.870 --> 01:24.952
I can't make it
this time.

01:25.000 --> 01:26.991
But...

01:27.040 --> 01:29.281
I made sure to get here
for your birthday party.

01:35.670 --> 01:38.298
Can you go grab some crayons
so we can color it?

01:38.340 --> 01:40.296
-Sure.
-Thank you, thank you.
Love you much.

01:51.730 --> 01:53.357
You cut your hair.

01:54.490 --> 01:55.946
I needed a change.

01:55.990 --> 01:57.605
Fits you.

01:59.070 --> 02:00.526
Thanks.

02:02.080 --> 02:06.119
So, how long
you here for?

02:07.750 --> 02:09.661
I'm here to stay.

02:20.050 --> 02:21.756
So what's happening
with the party?

02:23.930 --> 02:26.262
I don't know.
Are we supposed to do this?

02:26.310 --> 02:30.053
I could start by
picking him up in the morning.

02:30.100 --> 02:31.806
No, I'm talking about...

02:33.520 --> 02:35.317
I don't know how
it's supposed to work.

02:36.780 --> 02:39.908
As long as Blue's
in St. Jo,

02:39.950 --> 02:42.236
I'm staying in St. Jo.

02:45.490 --> 02:47.708
I'm going to be
in my son's life.

02:50.460 --> 02:52.701
And I'll do whatever
I have to to make it work.

03:01.680 --> 03:03.420
Dreams never die

03:03.470 --> 03:05.552
Take flight
As the world turns

03:05.600 --> 03:07.340
Dreams never die

03:07.390 --> 03:09.597
Take flight
As the world turns

03:09.640 --> 03:11.221
Keep the colors
In the lines

03:11.270 --> 03:13.511
Take flight

03:13.560 --> 03:14.891
Dreams never die

03:20.990 --> 03:23.902
Keep the colors
In the lines

03:23.950 --> 03:28.034
Keep the colors
In the lines, take flight

03:30.710 --> 03:32.996
-Hey, Aunt Violet.
-Hey, Charley.

03:33.040 --> 03:35.281
So, um... Hold on.

03:35.340 --> 03:37.456
Uh, I made
an appointment

03:37.500 --> 03:40.469
for Prosper to see the doctor
tomorrow morning.

03:40.510 --> 03:44.674
But now I am up to my eyeballs
in cherry pies,

03:44.720 --> 03:47.382
and I know if one of us don't
take that man,

03:47.430 --> 03:49.341
he ain't going,
so I need you to step in.

03:49.390 --> 03:51.472
I would, uh, but tomorrow

03:51.520 --> 03:53.226
I've got
a maintenance guy coming

03:53.270 --> 03:55.306
-to upgrade the turbine, so...
-Charley?

03:55.360 --> 03:57.681
Can't somebody else
over there at that mill

03:57.730 --> 03:59.140
meet with
the maintenance guy?

03:59.190 --> 04:01.238
Well, why can't Nova do it?

04:01.280 --> 04:03.692
Because Nova is shopping
and preparing

04:03.740 --> 04:05.526
for your daddy's
commemoration.

04:05.570 --> 04:08.152
If you two were talking,

04:08.200 --> 04:10.782
and you came down off your
high horse, you'd know that.

04:10.830 --> 04:12.400
So, back to Prosper.

04:12.460 --> 04:14.667
I need you to
pick him up by 10:00,

04:14.710 --> 04:17.247
'cause he has to be at
Westside Memorial by 10:30.

04:17.290 --> 04:18.871
All right?

04:18.920 --> 04:21.548
Thank you,
and I love you, baby.

04:24.510 --> 04:25.795
[beeps]

04:36.730 --> 04:39.938
This bitter bird

04:43.860 --> 04:48.115
What fruit it bears

04:50.580 --> 04:55.859
What good is love

04:57.580 --> 05:02.540
That no one shares?

05:07.090 --> 05:09.172
[continues, indistinct]

05:16.730 --> 05:19.472
The glow of a rose

05:20.770 --> 05:24.888
What good am I?

05:26.780 --> 05:31.570
I'm only close

05:33.410 --> 05:39.326
This bitter bird

05:41.050 --> 05:45.293
It feels so good

05:53.390 --> 05:55.176
We are out of pie boxes.

05:55.230 --> 05:56.879
No, there's more
in my trunk.

05:56.940 --> 05:58.896
My keys are over there
next to my purse.

05:58.940 --> 06:00.760
-Okay.
-[phone buzzes]

06:00.810 --> 06:02.721
-Hey, Nova.
-Hey.

06:02.780 --> 06:04.566
What are you doing,

06:04.610 --> 06:05.816
besides staring at that
beautiful ring on your finger?

06:05.860 --> 06:07.691
[chuckles]

06:07.740 --> 06:10.117
I'm getting a batch
of cherry pies out the door.

06:10.160 --> 06:12.617
How's it going? You got
everything for Friday?

06:12.660 --> 06:16.073
Yep. I was just seeing
what you were up to.

06:16.120 --> 06:20.124
-What you need, baby?
-I could use some
Aunt Vi wisdom.

06:20.170 --> 06:23.298
I don't know what this book
is supposed to be about.

06:23.340 --> 06:26.298
Now, they gave you
this book deal 'cause
they want to know about you.

06:26.340 --> 06:28.171
What's there
to figure out?

06:28.220 --> 06:30.211
I know. It...

06:30.260 --> 06:32.467
It's just a case
of writers' block.

06:32.510 --> 06:35.843
Girl, I ain't got no time
for writers' block.

06:35.890 --> 06:39.189
Too much to say
and not enough time to say it.

06:39.230 --> 06:41.186
Here's what I know:

06:41.230 --> 06:43.642
You're the only writer
I know from St. Jo.

06:43.690 --> 06:45.817
That means something.

06:45.860 --> 06:48.522
Shoot, you got stories
up and down this land.

06:48.570 --> 06:50.561
-Uh, got to go.
-[phone beeps]

06:50.610 --> 06:52.692
Hey, Miss Effie.

06:52.740 --> 06:55.197
I know it's a mess, but it'll
all be clean in about an hour.

06:55.240 --> 06:56.992
It's not about the mess.

06:57.040 --> 06:59.668
Your time's up.

06:59.710 --> 07:01.996
The Wednesday Supper Club is
out there pouting like puppies.

07:02.040 --> 07:05.749
I have the kitchen from 8:00
to 5:00 on Wednesdays.

07:05.800 --> 07:08.792
It's on the calendar. I've got
another two batches to go.

07:08.840 --> 07:11.889
Well, there must be some sort
of misunderstanding,

07:11.930 --> 07:14.501
because they've been
doing their supper club

07:14.560 --> 07:16.676
for as long
as I've been here.

07:16.720 --> 07:19.518
Good, churchgoing
people.

07:22.730 --> 07:25.563
Miss Effie,
we have an agreement.

07:25.610 --> 07:27.475
It seems that the checks

07:27.530 --> 07:29.486
I've been writing the church
are clearing just fine.

07:29.530 --> 07:31.771
I'm sure the good Lord
appreciates that,

07:31.820 --> 07:35.654
but they'll still be coming in
on Wednesdays at 4:00 pm.

07:35.700 --> 07:39.192
So, whatever you need to do
to finish up...

07:44.080 --> 07:45.957
"Good Lord," my ass.

07:48.210 --> 07:50.508
Right, so with Sam at 41%

07:50.550 --> 07:53.292
and his sister Frances
at 35,

07:53.340 --> 07:57.049
you'd better believe
that 6% divide put a rift
between those two.

07:57.100 --> 08:00.888
There's a history of tension
on both sides of that family.

08:00.930 --> 08:02.932
That pool of investors
at 80/0"

08:02.980 --> 08:05.517
one of them makes more money
than he reports,

08:05.560 --> 08:07.437
and, surprise, surprise,
another one

08:07.480 --> 08:10.483
has a propensity
for prostitutes.

08:10.530 --> 08:12.191
Of course they do.

08:12.240 --> 08:15.368
Oh, and, um, Frances' sons,
Jacob and Paul,

08:15.410 --> 08:17.025
they're splitting
their 50/0.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.287
I mean, you know that
already.

08:19.330 --> 08:22.367
I don't know.
Those Boudreaux boys,
they keep it clean.

08:22.410 --> 08:24.162
Well, when it comes
to Jacob,

08:24.210 --> 08:26.166
there's no way he has
a spotless record.

08:26.210 --> 08:28.087
I'll keep digging
on my end.

08:28.130 --> 08:30.121
What else you got
on Sam's son?

08:30.170 --> 08:32.923
Ooh. Colton Landry,

08:32.970 --> 08:36.383
Sam's only son, with 10%.

08:36.430 --> 08:39.718
He's this hotshot
patent lawyer In Houston.

08:39.770 --> 08:43.763
Iw League. Wife and kids.
Goes to church every Sunday.

08:43.810 --> 08:46.472
Oh, and he also has
a really nice

08:46.520 --> 08:49.853
piece on the side
for the last five years.

08:49.900 --> 08:51.982
-What a piece of work.
-Mm.

08:52.030 --> 08:55.102
But everything else
seems to be pretty legit.

08:55.160 --> 08:57.310
No, there's got
to be more.

08:57.370 --> 08:59.907
This family's dirty.
I've seen it.

09:05.370 --> 09:08.624
Four stories in,
and he's finally asleep.

09:11.510 --> 09:15.253
He was, uh, telling me
about his field trip,

09:16.590 --> 09:18.251
asked if
I could chaperone.

09:20.260 --> 09:22.467
I already told his teacher
I'd take him.

09:29.480 --> 09:31.778
He's got plastic
under his sheets.

09:35.740 --> 09:37.776
He started
wetting the bed

09:39.120 --> 09:40.485
a few weeks
after you left.

09:46.830 --> 09:48.536
Why didn't you tell me?

09:48.580 --> 09:50.241
He didn't want
nobody to know.

09:52.130 --> 09:55.668
-He embarrassed by it.
-That's something I should know.

09:57.590 --> 09:58.921
Yeah.

10:01.680 --> 10:04.342
Blue didn't want
to celebrate his birthday

10:06.770 --> 10:10.854
because of what happened to Pops
and his party last year.

10:12.820 --> 10:16.859
But I suggested we do this
bonfire thing for Pop instead.

10:16.900 --> 10:19.198
It's got a spiritual
meaning to it.

10:19.240 --> 10:21.117
Something like that.

10:23.700 --> 10:26.578
Said it'd help
to make his birthday feel

10:28.370 --> 10:29.871
happy again.

10:39.470 --> 10:41.040
I know that
this is been...

10:43.430 --> 10:44.556
hard...

10:46.810 --> 10:48.516
for you and Blue.

10:53.110 --> 10:54.975
I want to
make things right.

10:58.320 --> 11:00.276
I want to
figure this out.

11:00.320 --> 11:02.697
-You could've told me
you was coming.
-I tried.

11:02.740 --> 11:05.368
You wouldn't listen.

11:21.470 --> 11:23.006
We'll figure it out.

11:38.690 --> 11:42.023
They're here somewhere.
I...

11:43.740 --> 11:46.072
I, uh, I...

11:46.120 --> 11:49.499
found my insurance card
with the medical records.

11:49.540 --> 11:52.998
Well, we've got about half
an hour to get on over there.

11:53.040 --> 11:55.497
Claire had this system...

11:57.130 --> 11:59.621
but I never understood it.

12:01.380 --> 12:05.749
I mean, it's got to be
in here somewhere.

12:31.330 --> 12:33.537
Mr. Prosper, you play?

12:36.920 --> 12:38.876
Yeah.

12:38.920 --> 12:41.718
Yeah, your daddy used to find me
down on Frenchman Street

12:41.760 --> 12:44.001
jamming with the fellas.

12:45.260 --> 12:47.000
Yeah.

12:47.050 --> 12:49.382
Yeah, it's been
a while now.

12:52.020 --> 12:53.976
A long while.

12:55.850 --> 12:58.728
I don't mean to rush you,
Mr. Prosper,

12:58.770 --> 13:02.399
but I will face Aunt Vi's wrath
if we don't make it to
this appointment.

13:06.740 --> 13:09.527
Can I have just a second?

13:11.330 --> 13:12.786
Yeah.

13:17.330 --> 13:19.582
Your aunties always
used to talk about

13:19.630 --> 13:22.167
about you were
so headstrong,

13:22.210 --> 13:25.043
and nothing could stand
in your way.

13:25.090 --> 13:29.129
Used to sing your praises
to anybody that would listen.

13:36.810 --> 13:38.300
I miss her.

13:43.940 --> 13:45.737
Me too.

13:47.360 --> 13:49.442
Now all I've got is...

13:50.910 --> 13:53.242
a cane and a bad back.

14:00.670 --> 14:04.254
Maybe we can reschedule
for tomorrow,

14:04.300 --> 14:07.929
and I can
come over early

14:07.970 --> 14:10.256
and help you find
that paperwork.

14:11.760 --> 14:14.092
I'm sorry
to waste your time.

14:15.230 --> 14:16.515
It's all right.

14:18.900 --> 14:21.300
Marvin's in _
the freezer section.

14:21.360 --> 14:23.396
I'll be right behind you.

14:23.440 --> 14:25.146
I'm telling you, Vi, there's got
to be a better way than this.

14:25.190 --> 14:27.943
We're doing fine.
Just don't worry, now.

14:27.990 --> 14:30.447
You need a real
delivery truck.

14:30.490 --> 14:32.651
I can't be spending
that kind of money.

14:32.700 --> 14:34.782
You ain't got to
spend nothing.

14:36.790 --> 14:38.280
[grunts]

14:46.130 --> 14:48.428
Vi, some of these pies
look smushed.

14:48.470 --> 14:50.677
-You want me to
take them all in?
-No. No, no.

14:50.720 --> 14:52.676
I'm coming. Let me see.

15:05.150 --> 15:06.981
[groans]

15:07.030 --> 15:09.772
My belly hurts.

15:09.820 --> 15:12.402
How many slices
did you eat?

15:12.450 --> 15:14.907
[scoffs]
That's why.

15:14.950 --> 15:16.360
Mm-hmm.

15:16.410 --> 15:18.321
I'm going
to the bathroom.

15:20.620 --> 15:22.781
Pop,
I can do it myself.

15:25.050 --> 15:26.756
Wash your hands.

15:32.260 --> 15:34.000
I want to go
on the field trip.

15:34.050 --> 15:36.678
I already told you,
I talked to his teacher.

15:36.720 --> 15:40.804
-Why can't we both go?
-Like I said, I already talked
to Miss Santiago.

15:40.850 --> 15:44.809
I shouldn't have
to ask permi55ion

15:44.860 --> 15:47.021
to spend time
with my son.

15:50.320 --> 15:51.651
Our son.

15:54.530 --> 15:56.521
I'm still his mom.

15:58.200 --> 16:00.953
And you're still
his dad.

16:02.710 --> 16:05.247
-That hasn't changed.
-Everything changed.

16:08.460 --> 16:11.213
Everything changed.

16:32.110 --> 16:33.850
Hey.
What you got there?

16:33.910 --> 16:35.480
Wait, hold on.
Let me help.

16:35.530 --> 16:37.657
-Food for the bonfire.
-All right.

16:37.700 --> 16:39.782
We're supposed to have
some folks come build it.

16:39.830 --> 16:41.570
What are you doing here?

16:41.620 --> 16:43.030
Today the farm
is my classroom.

16:43.080 --> 16:44.741
I got some students
coming out.

16:44.790 --> 16:46.280
I'm gonna teach 'em all
about fertilization.

16:46.330 --> 16:47.831
Fascinating.

16:47.880 --> 16:48.995
I'm sure
that'll keep 'em awake.

16:49.050 --> 16:51.291
Oh-ho! You got jokes!

16:51.340 --> 16:54.298
Oh, wait a minute. I'm as
fascinating as Professor X.

16:54.340 --> 16:55.921
Okay? My students
love me.

16:55.970 --> 16:58.256
-You keep telling yourself that.
-Wow!

16:58.300 --> 17:01.178
I know you're a great teacher.
Ra even told me so.

17:01.220 --> 17:03.472
Oh.

17:03.520 --> 17:06.853
Wasn't that long ago,
your brother was sitting
in my class.

17:06.900 --> 17:10.722
Now look at him. Almost looks
like your daddy out there.

17:14.490 --> 17:16.481
All right, lady.

17:16.530 --> 17:19.442
I'm gonna head over there.
I'll see you tonight.

17:29.130 --> 17:31.041
[doorbell rings]

17:31.090 --> 17:33.968
-Micah, your dad's here.
-Okay.

17:38.600 --> 17:41.057
-[door opens, closes]
-[Davis] What's up?

17:41.100 --> 17:44.479
-So what's the plan?
-It's a surprise.

17:44.520 --> 17:46.385
Okay.

17:46.440 --> 17:48.806
Actually, I'm gonna grab
my phone right quick.

17:48.860 --> 17:50.509
-Be right back.
-Okay.

17:53.190 --> 17:54.430
Hey, Charley.

17:54.490 --> 17:56.811
How are you, Davis?

17:58.910 --> 18:00.775
The work never stops
for you, huh?

18:00.830 --> 18:03.993
No, it does not.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.996
You really added
a nice touch to the place.

18:09.920 --> 18:12.206
Nothing's changed since
the last time you saw it.

18:14.300 --> 18:16.416
Say, what's going on
at Ralph Angel's place?

18:16.470 --> 18:18.506
Micah said you guys
were doing something over there?

18:18.550 --> 18:20.541
Yeah, Grandpa's
commemoration.

18:21.760 --> 18:23.557
Oh.

18:25.850 --> 18:27.761
Well, you two
better get going.

18:27.810 --> 18:30.472
-Have fun.
-Thanks. Bye.

18:32.110 --> 18:34.021
-Ready to go.
-All right.

18:45.700 --> 18:48.407
What's all this?
What you doing in here?

18:48.460 --> 18:50.667
Just one of Nova's
healthy recipes.

18:50.710 --> 18:53.087
Ooh, ooh, ooh.
Now, check it.

18:53.130 --> 18:56.122
Boogie was telling me about
this old delivery truck
in a junkyard.

18:56.170 --> 19:00.334
Says all it needs is
a couple hundred dollars
to fix it on up.

19:00.390 --> 19:02.506
Put a refrigerator unit
in there.

19:02.550 --> 19:05.769
No more smushed pies,
no more lost inventory.

19:05.810 --> 19:08.267
I hear what you're saying,

19:08.310 --> 19:10.301
and I appreciate
all this effort,

19:10.350 --> 19:12.432
but I want to do this
my way,

19:12.480 --> 19:14.766
and I ain't ready to buy
no delivery truck.

19:14.820 --> 19:16.356
No, baby, I'm buying it.

19:16.400 --> 19:18.277
Oh, no, no, no.

19:18.320 --> 19:20.606
I mean for you to keep
your wallet it in your pocket.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.366
Uh-uh. See, I already
got a guy, right?

19:22.410 --> 19:24.366
He going to put
the logo on a magnet.

19:24.410 --> 19:27.152
Slap that sucker
on the side of this thing,

19:27.200 --> 19:28.781
and the whole world
will know

19:28.830 --> 19:31.993
that Vi's Prize Pies
have arrived.

19:32.040 --> 19:35.828
Well, I appreciate it.

19:35.880 --> 19:39.259
But I started
this business myself,

19:39.300 --> 19:42.633
and... that's the way
I want to keep it.

19:42.680 --> 19:45.888
Ain't no shame in letting
loved ones pitch in.

19:45.930 --> 19:47.921
It's all beautiful,
baby.

19:47.970 --> 19:49.267
Really is.

19:51.690 --> 19:54.648
But at this point in my life,
I don't want to owe nobody
nothing.

19:55.860 --> 19:56.929
"Owe"?

19:57.900 --> 19:59.561
[scoffs]

20:04.410 --> 20:06.480
You know Jimmy Dale
bought this house,

20:07.950 --> 20:10.453
and he let me know it
every time

20:10.500 --> 20:12.616
I stepped foot
through that door.

20:12.670 --> 20:15.662
Held money over my head
like he owned me.

20:15.710 --> 20:18.497
Yeah, but me and Jimmy Dale
are like night and day,
so don't go there.

20:18.550 --> 20:22.042
Now, look, all I'm trying
to tell you is that this truck

20:22.090 --> 20:24.217
is going to do
a whole lot of...

20:27.220 --> 20:30.348
Baby, I see you out here.
You're doing some great things.

20:32.560 --> 20:35.302
I also see that you need
